{"TopicId":187173,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Plasma Thrusters Enhanced with Chemical Rockets","CreatedByName":"Cheif Operations Director","CreatedById":183218,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-13T23:56:06Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Cheif Operations Director","CreatedById":183218,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-13T23:56:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EOut of curiosity, why not make a chemical rocket that takes a neutrally charged atom and ionizes it (normal plasma thrust based off of this (\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ionization_energy\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ionization_energy\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E) take that negatively charged ion and confine it to a few atoms thick of a stream via magnets (pretty much the inverse of the magnetic nozzle mentioned in the below thread) \u00A0and then inject a positively charged fuel for a super heated chemical reaction in addition to the plasma thrust? You could even use the fuel to (ever so slightly) cool down the systems while the rocket is operating to prevent suddenly unplanned disassemblies.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003Ebasically inverse that nozzle right here\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://images.search.yahoo.com/images/view;_ylt=AwrJ7JYjS1Ndo94ASgDBGOd_;_ylu=X3oDMTByMjB0aG5zBGNvbG8DYmYxBHBvcwMxBHZ0aWQDBHNlYwNzYw--?p=vasmir\u0026amp;back=https%3A%2F%2Fsearch.yahoo.com%2Fsearch%3Fp%3Dvasmir%26ei%3DUTF-8\u0026amp;no=1\u0026amp;fr=ipad\u0026amp;h=538\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;imgurl=www.adastrarocket.com%2Fimages%2Fvasimr.jpg\u0026amp;rurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.adastrarocket.com%2Faarc%2FVASIMR\u0026amp;size=167KB\u0026amp;name=Our\u002BEngine\u002B%7C\u002BAd\u002BAstra\u002BRocket\u0026amp;oid=OIP.GsYVg3OCb0XTl3otHHh1gQHaE-\u0026amp;tt=Our\u002BEngine\u002B%7C\u002BAd\u002BAstra\u002BRocket\u0026amp;sigr=118flh152\u0026amp;sigi=1176d8m4i\u0026amp;sigb=11hraf1qq\u0026amp;sign=10skd8o6n\u0026amp;sigt=10skd8o6n\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://images.search.yahoo.com/images/view;_ylt=AwrJ7JYjS1Ndo94ASgDBGOd_;_ylu=X3oDMTByMjB0aG5zBGNvbG8DYmYxBHBvcwMxBHZ0aWQDBHNlYwNzYw--?p=vasmir\u0026amp;back=https%3A%2F%2Fsearch.yahoo.com%2Fsearch%3Fp%3Dvasmir%26ei%3DUTF-8\u0026amp;no=1\u0026amp;fr=ipad\u0026amp;h=538\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;imgurl=www.adastrarocket.com%2Fimages%2Fvasimr.jpg\u0026amp;rurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.adastrarocket.com%2Faarc%2FVASIMR\u0026amp;size=167KB\u0026amp;name=Our\u002BEngine\u002B|\u002BAd\u002BAstra\u002BRocket\u0026amp;oid=OIP.GsYVg3OCb0XTl3otHHh1gQHaE-\u0026amp;tt=Our\u002BEngine\u002B|\u002BAd\u002BAstra\u002BRocket\u0026amp;sigr=118flh152\u0026amp;sigi=1176d8m4i\u0026amp;sigb=11hraf1qq\u0026amp;sign=10skd8o6n\u0026amp;sigt=10skd8o6n\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUse the magnet to get the plasma into a small beam accelerating it due to the pressure even more. Then inject the positive ions, let\u2019s call it LOX for now. (let\u2019s suppose you ionize hydrogen or helium)\u00A0Then expand the nozzle into a combo between a chemical and magnetic nozzle. Perhaps double layered, one to take the brunt of the heat (perhaps ablative due to the high heat) and then the magnetic one to keep non-reacted ions from reacting with the ablative rocket nozzle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EI should clarify that I know temperature\u2019s will get very high and that is a problem, I also do not know a ton about plasma\u00A0engines, I was just looking into them a bit. I was reading this page (\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plasma_propulsion_engine\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plasma_propulsion_engine\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0) and thought that perhaps if you reduced the amount of required ions you may be able to reduce the electricity needed and thus with the chemical addition be able to get\u00A0a better\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022 title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInspired by this thread\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022197504\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3764551777\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/186968-rocket-plumes-and-magnetic-nozzles/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-08-14T04:40:02Z\u0022 title=\u002208/14/2019 04:40  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 14, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Cheif Operations Director\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheif Operations Director","CreatedById":183218,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T02:21:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002288.32\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 width=\u0022869\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/608819058787352665/611020858583941142/screenshot.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomething like this (excuse the bad sketch) the purple is your run of the mill plasma thruster, the it pushes the ionized fuel (purple) into the combustion chamber where a small amount of LOX is added for combustion.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AngrybobH","CreatedById":165814,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T02:31:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is similar to something I have wondered about for some time. Why can\u0027t you boost a rocket engine with a magnetic field? Turns out rocket exhaust isn\u0027t that ionized. But, how could you increase that? would there be a benefit? What if you already had the power to run the field in your payload? I am nearly completely out of my element answering any of those questions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheif Operations Director","CreatedById":183218,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T02:48:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650258\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565749874\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165814\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AngrybobH\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, AngrybobH said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is similar to something I have wondered about for some time. Why can\u0027t you boost a rocket engine with a magnetic field? Turns out rocket exhaust isn\u0027t that ionized. But, how could you increase that? would there be a benefit? What if you already had the power to run the field in your payload? I am nearly completely out of my element answering any of those questions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYea but if we intentionally ionized the air we could make hypergonic fuel in flight with hydrogen and oxygen and get a ton of heat and pressure to accelerate a small amount of propellant (in theory, theory in the non scientific sense)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nothalogh","CreatedById":139345,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T05:01:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650252\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565749282\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183218\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cheif Operations Director\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Cheif Operations Director said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/608819058787352665/611020858583941142/screenshot.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002288.32\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 width=\u0022869\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/608819058787352665/611020858583941142/screenshot.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomething like this (excuse the bad sketch) the purple is your run of the mill plasma thruster, the it pushes the ionized fuel (purple) into the combustion chamber where a small amount of LOX is added for combustion.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe the LOX would just get immediately ionized and just join the outward flow of reaction mass, only being able to chemically combine with your fuel long after it has left the nozzle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe only net effect I can forsee is a lower \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Specific Impulse (rocketry) or Internet Service Provider\u0022\u003EISP\u003C/abbr\u003E due to a higher molecular mass of the exhaust.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheif Operations Director","CreatedById":183218,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T05:03:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650309\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565758893\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139345\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nothalogh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Nothalogh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe the LOX would just get immediately ionized and just join the outward flow of reaction mass, only being able to chemically combine with your fuel long after it has left the nozzle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe only net effect I can forsee is a lower \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Specific Impulse (rocketry) or Internet Service Provider\u0022\u003EISP\u003C/abbr\u003E due to a higher molecular mass of the exhaust.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhy would it get immediately ionized?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nothalogh","CreatedById":139345,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T05:06:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650310\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565759035\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183218\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cheif Operations Director\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Cheif Operations Director said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhy would it get immediately ionized?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause the local environmental conditions of PLASMA tend to preclude chemical bonds forming at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650311\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565759179\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you have some much power to accelerate, why complicate the engine with chemistry? Just ionize it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhere else will the toilet flush to?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T05:06:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you have some much power to accelerate, why complicate the engine with chemistry? Just ionize it by heating.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-08-14T05:06:30Z\u0022 title=\u002208/14/2019 05:06  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 14, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheif Operations Director","CreatedById":183218,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T05:08:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650311\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565759179\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you have some much power to accelerate, why complicate the engine with chemistry? Just ionize it by heating.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo get a high thrust?\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650312\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565759176\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139345\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nothalogh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Nothalogh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPLASMA tend to preclude chemical bonds forming at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhat if you put it right at the line so some of it was plasma and some of it was not?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nothalogh","CreatedById":139345,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T05:09:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650313\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565759295\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183218\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cheif Operations Director\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Cheif Operations Director said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo get a high thrust?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt the cost of reduced specific impulse\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheif Operations Director","CreatedById":183218,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T05:10:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650314\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565759351\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139345\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nothalogh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Nothalogh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt the cost of reduced specific impulse\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes but most of the advantages would still be their right? I mean the super hot gases and plasma accelerating the explosive material out even faster of the nozzle creating more pressure?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T05:11:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650312\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565759176\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139345\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nothalogh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Nothalogh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhere else will the toilet flush to?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn a small ship toilet is to be flushed into kitchen, they are just two sides of a coin. Just recycle in between.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650313\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565759295\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183218\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cheif Operations Director\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Cheif Operations Director said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo get a high thrust?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can ionize elements\u00A0 of any atomic number and mass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-08-14T05:12:00Z\u0022 title=\u002208/14/2019 05:12  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 14, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheif Operations Director","CreatedById":183218,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T05:12:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650317\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565759511\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can ionize elements\u00A0 of any atomic number and mass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nothalogh","CreatedById":139345,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T05:13:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650316\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565759451\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183218\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cheif Operations Director\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Cheif Operations Director said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes but most of the advantages would still be their right? I mean the super hot gases and plasma accelerating the explosive material out even faster of the nozzle creating more pressure?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell any chemical reaction would have to occur after the plasma had condensed back to gas, which would be outside of your engine bell\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T05:13:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, ionize a piece of iron when you need high atomic mass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheif Operations Director","CreatedById":183218,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T05:13:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650320\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565759585\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139345\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nothalogh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Nothalogh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell any chemical reaction would have to occur after the plasma had condensed back to gas, which would be outside of your engine bell\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo Plasma\u0027s are always incapable of bonding even with other plasma\u0027s?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565759593\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, ionize a piece of iron when you need high atomic mass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwait what? Im not following you sorry\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nothalogh","CreatedById":139345,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T05:16:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650323\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565759625\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183218\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cheif Operations Director\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Cheif Operations Director said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo Plasma\u0027s are always incapable of bonding even with other plasma\u0027s?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the state of plasma, the electrons are otherwise indisposed, electrons do the bonding.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf there is bonding going on in your plasma, you have FUSION, and that means your containment and cooling system is about to have a problem\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheif Operations Director","CreatedById":183218,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T05:19:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650324\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565759773\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139345\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nothalogh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Nothalogh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the state of plasma, the electrons are otherwise indisposed, electrons do the bonding.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf there is bonding going on in your plasma, you have FUSION, and that means your containment and cooling system is about to have a problem\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlright, I need to sleep I will continue tomorrow sorry\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T05:35:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650316\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565759451\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183218\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cheif Operations Director\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Cheif Operations Director said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes but most of the advantages would still be their right? I mean the super hot gases and plasma accelerating the explosive material out even faster of the nozzle creating more pressure?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProblem is that you need an power source. think the afterburner will be pretty heavy and have an minimum power demand who is also pretty high.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nWhy not just stage and use an ion engine or other engines who is high isp but low trust.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scotius","CreatedById":57622,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T06:25:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is a dilemma as old as rocketry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUsually you want your engine as efficient as possible. Thus, Isp is king.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut... you also want your engine powerful enough to move your craft at reasonable pace. For that you need good thrust.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurrent engines we can built, can have one. Electric engines give high fuel efficiency, chemical rockets give high power.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow can we combine the two? Ideas range from:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLiterally combine two separate engine sets on one rocket. Chemical engines for high energy maneuvers, electric engine for interplanetary cruise...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo crazy sci-fi ideas like Saltwater rocket or Orion.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0In-between lie more sensible projects like NERVA, VASIMR, MagnetoPlasmaDynamic thrusters or Fusion Pulse engines.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut hybridising ion and chemical engine? It looks kind of \u0027Meh\u0027 to me. It will significantly increase the mass by adding chemical fuel (with necessary tankage and plumbing), while crippling the biggest advantage of the electric engine (high Isp!), without increasing thrust appreciably.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T11:24:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/183218-cheif-operations-director/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022183218\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/183218-cheif-operations-director/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Cheif Operations Director\u003C/a\u003E, I think you\u2019re looking for augmented thrusters. The transfer of additional energy is through mundane resistojet or arcjet systems, and they also replace the usual catalyst bed in a hydrazine thruster.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheif Operations Director","CreatedById":183218,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T11:53:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650347\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565763901\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scotius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Scotius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut hybridising ion and chemical engine? It looks kind of \u0027Meh\u0027 to me. It will significantly increase the mass by adding chemical fuel (with necessary tankage and plumbing), while crippling the biggest advantage of the electric engine (high Isp!), without increasing thrust appreciably.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhat part of this design causes the high Isp. I want to make sure we are on the same page here\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650411\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565781875\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n28 minutes ago, DDE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/183218-cheif-operations-director/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022183218\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/183218-cheif-operations-director/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Cheif Operations Director\u003C/a\u003E, I think you\u2019re looking for augmented thrusters. The transfer of additional energy is through mundane resistojet or arcjet systems, and they also replace the usual catalyst bed in a hydrazine thruster.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes I think it may be the same idea. A sort of combo between the two\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650333\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565760954\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nafterburner will be pretty heavy and have an minimum power demand who is also pretty high.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would be your run of the mill chemical rocket\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650333\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565760954\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProblem is that you need an power source.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNulcear reactor perhaps?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nothalogh","CreatedById":139345,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T14:30:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650421\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565783586\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183218\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cheif Operations Director\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Cheif Operations Director said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhat part of this design causes the high Isp\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe atomic mass of whatever you are shoveling into the it, turning into plasma, and then magnetically accelerating out the rear.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe lower the mass, the higher the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Specific Impulse (rocketry) or Internet Service Provider\u0022\u003EISP\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheif Operations Director","CreatedById":183218,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T14:34:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650468\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565793053\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139345\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nothalogh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Nothalogh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe atomic mass of whatever you are shoveling into the it, turning into plasma, and then magnetically accelerating out the rear.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe lower the mass, the higher the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Specific Impulse (rocketry) or Internet Service Provider\u0022\u003EISP\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk, that is what I thought so how would I be costing a large decrease in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Specific Impulse (rocketry) or Internet Service Provider\u0022\u003EISP\u003C/abbr\u003E if I am expelling a mostly small amount of fuel out of the back? Remember I need 2 H and 1 O for H20 so If we suppose I am expelling 1,000,000 hyrodgen atoms a second I need 500,000 oxygens. I am getting that acceleration from the base plasma thruster, I am then combining the already very fast particles in gaseous form. It transitions from a plasma to a gas in the combustion chamber.and then creates even more pressure, not less.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nothalogh","CreatedById":139345,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-14T14:37:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223650471\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565793285\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183218\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cheif Operations Director\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Cheif Operations Director said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt transitions from a plasma to a gas in the \u003Cs\u003Ecombustion\u003C/s\u003E chamber\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027d better hope it doesn\u0027t, or it won\u0027t make it through the mag accelerator.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}